{#- §06 WHICH (three-way disambiguation → cmp table + 3 H3 prose) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-migcleanup-which">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§06</span><span class="idx__t">Which engagement is yours</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:12px;">Migration cleanup, balance repair, or file cleanup?</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:62ch;">Three related engagements, told apart by where the damage came from. The headings below name each; the table shows when each fits.</p>
    <table class="cmp" data-viz="comparison-table" data-viz-state="FINAL">
      <caption class="sr-only">Migration cleanup compared with balance repair and file cleanup, by dimension.</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
          <th scope="col" class="us">Migration cleanup</th>
          <th scope="col">Balance repair</th>
          <th scope="col">File cleanup</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for row in which %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th>
          <td class="us" data-col="Migration cleanup"><strong>{{ row.cleanup | safe }}</strong></td>
          <td data-col="Balance repair">{{ row.balance | safe }}</td>
          <td data-col="File cleanup">{{ row.file | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="prose read" style="margin-top:36px;">
      <h3>Migration cleanup</h3>
      <p>This page. The conversion damaged the file broadly &mdash; balances <em>and</em> lists, items, integrations, inventory, and workflows. The right engagement when the whole file feels wrong after a Desktop-to-Online or software-to-QuickBooks move.</p>
      <h3>Balance repair</h3>
      <p>When <em>only</em> the numbers are off &mdash; opening balances, reconciliation, AR/AP totals &mdash; but the lists, items, and structure came across fine. The narrower, faster, cheaper fix.</p>
      <h3>File cleanup</h3>
      <p>When the problems <em>aren&rsquo;t</em> from a migration &mdash; they accumulated over time in a file you&rsquo;ve had all along. Reconciliation drift, messy categorization, corruption. See <a href="/quickbooks/cleanup/?intent=qb-cleanup">QuickBooks file cleanup</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

